<dl id="n03153a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n03" href="#n03153a">N03 (VI.B.3)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n03all.htm#n03153a"> 153(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> It is not true that / Pop was homosexual / he had been arrested / at the request of some / nursemaids to whom / he had temporarily / exposed himself / in the Temple gardens <small>Blue</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n03153a"><li>FW 33.19 </li><li><a href="../../flex/b/lexb.htm#n03153a">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/b/l39b.htm#n03153a">1939</a> &nbsp;<a href="../../flex/z/lexfh.htm#n03153a">FH IX</a> </li><li><ms href="#n03153a">MS BL 47472-97v</ms> </li><li>JJA 45:003 <a name="b10d" href="../../FF/fdra/bda.htm#b10d">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/b/b10d.htm#n03153a">Draft: I.2&sect;1.0</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">The irony of chance wills it that the late <font color="green">[father of Oscar Wilde&apos;s wife, Constance Lloyd,]</font> had been more than suspected of sexual viciousness <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> <font color="green">[In an appendix Robert Ross adds]</font> The charge against Horatio Lloyd was of a normal kind. It was for <mark>exposing himself to nursemaids in the gardens of the Temple</mark>. <small> Frank Harris, <a name="FHOW2" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#FHOW2"><cite title="source">Oscar Wilde His Life and Confessions</cite></a> (1918) 587, 608</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
